name: SAMSAM JERO TELAGA 2
address: Jl. Wibisana Bar. No.26, Pemecutan Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1: Great place if you love suckling pig and the typical Balinese warung. When I came here there were quite many people queueing, mostly Gojek/grab drivers delivering takeaways. No parking spot, the warung is in intersection, so not recommended to bring car here. They have small space for dine in, only +/-4 tables, so it's best to do takeaway. Serve fairly fast, despite many people ordering. This photo I post is the IDR 20k menu. As a famous warung, this place is still humbly reasonably priced and portioned.
review 2:
I take away Samsam Babi Guling, couldn't say anything about the taste because its just too good in my tounge!

The place is quite narrow and no parking for car, so i recommend you to ride motorcycle if you want to go.

The Samsam Guling is the best part, skin is very dry and crispy, and the fat will melt in your mouth. Lawar taste not so strong but it is good since we will focus on the Samsam Guling. Don't forget to eat the chili pieces, it will make your food tastier.

I will recommend this place to some of you who come you Bali. This is totally authentic local delicacy!

See you again!
